  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Balke - Shaping the Future of Northern Chad by Enhancing Security and Stability</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project addresses stabilization and the promotion of human security in communities in the north of Chad that are affected by marginalization, a lack of basic social services, and challenges related to irregular migration towards gold mining areas in Tibesti and southern Libya, including trafficking and recruitment into armed groups. The project works along two main axes: supporting communities in addressing root causes of instability by providing alternative means of livelihood and participation in decision-making processes; and enhancing institutional capacities to secure and manage Chadian borders by developing stronger community engagement and more coherent approaches to border management.</narrative>
  </description>
